      "text": [
        "568 - وَقَالَ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ: «مَنْ خَافَ عَلَى نَفْسِهِ مِنْ وَجْدٍ بِمُصِيبَةٍ فَلْيُفِضْ مِنْ دُمُوعِهِ فَإِنَّهُ يَسْكُنُ عَنْهُ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.568 - Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) said: \"Whoever fears being overwhelmed by grief due to a calamity should let their tears flow, for it will bring them relief.\""
        ]
      }
    },
